Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Bring a #medium pot{} of @water{}(salted) to a boil.

Place packet of @pesto{1/2%cup} in a #cup{} of warm water to bring to room temperature.

In a #large bowl{}, combine @ground beef{10%oz}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, half the @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, half the @garlic powder{1%tsp}, half the @Italian seasoning{1/2%tbsp}, @water{2%tbsp}, @salt{1/2%tsp}, and @pepper{}. Form into 10-12 1 1⁄2-inch meatballs (20-24 for 4).

Place meatballs on a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}. Roast on top rack until browned and cooked through, ~{14-16%minutes}.

> Ground Meat is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.

Once water is boiling, add @spaghetti{6%oz} to pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Drain, then return to pot.

Toss with @butter{2%tbsp} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. TIP: If you added any other items to your meal (apps, sides, and/or dessert), you can get started on them now!

While pasta cooks, melt @butter{1%tbsp} in a #large pan{}(preferably nonstick) over medium heat. Add remaining @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup} and cook, stirring, until golden brown, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Turn off heat. Transfer to a #small bowl{}; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Wipe out pan.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in pan used for panko over medium-high heat. Add @crushed tomatoes{1%can}, remaining @garlic powder{1%tsp}, remaining @Italian seasoning{1/2%tbsp}, @sugar{1/4%tsp}, @salt{1/2%tsp}, and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until sauce is warmed through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Serve spaghetti, meatballs, toasted panko, red sauce, pesto, @balsamic glaze{5%tsp}, and @Parmesan cheese{3%tbsp} family style and let everyone build their own plates (if you've got some on hand, serve with @?chili flakes{} from your pantry if desired).

> Bring dinnertime joy to everyone at the table with spaghetti, beef meatballs, and two sauces: marinara and pesto. We've included tons of toppings, so everyone can make their perfect pasta bowl. Order broccoli for a veggie side or swap in ground turkey and be a meatball hero!